    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "No luck on this one so I'm unassigning myself.\r\n\r\nMy final thoughts were: rather than mining the blocks in block data generator which is not something we want to do, we can simply get the block processors to not validate the public state roots since the tests shouldn't care about the public state roots and we're only asserting the private state roots stay the same after reorg.\r\n\r\nHowever the way we construct the validators means it's very difficult to mock them, not sure if possible at all. Dropping this one and happy to have a chat with the next person who picks it up :)",
